One of my favorite pictures from her birth. You can even see the cord still attached😍We chose to delay cord cutting to make sure she got all HER blood back into her little body. Since that's exactly what it is. We waited until it stopped pulsing, which was 12 minutes. Did you delay cord clamping? Most hospitals and birth centers are starting to do it for all babies unless there's a medical reason otherwise. A few of the proven benefits are neurodevelopment boosts, reduced risk of anemia, increased blood volume- almost 32% more than immediate cutting of the cord!!!(😳), and such great benefits for babies born early. Pretty cool. But, I just love this picture. •
